ep of the entire file to make sure everything checks out... The knowledge file looks solid overall. One last thing I'm noticing—the `allowNullValue` description simplifies \"Mapインタフェースの実装クラス\" to \"Mapインタフェース実装,\" which is a minor condensation but still accurate. And in s2, the note about \"設定値なし\" needs checking against the source...\n\nLooking at the `trimPolicy` note in s1, the source provides detailed guidance about full-width spaces not being trimmed, but the knowledge file appears to cut off mid-sentence. The knowledge version seems incomplete compared to the full explanation in the source material.\n\nThe source establishes a broader principle: any character with a code value greater than '\\u0020' won't be trimmed, using full-width spaces as the primary example. The knowledge file only captures the specific case of full-width spaces without conveying this general rule, which could matter if someone needs to handle other wide characters correctly.\n\nThis is worth flagging as a minor omission—the general principle got lost when the knowledge was condensed to just the example.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19933,"cache_read_input_tokens":35069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19933,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c962864a-fdfc-4fb3-98e5-a37405caf92f","uuid":"6435bfa5-045e-4ab1-981c-21586d776864"}
